library(gapminder)
library(ggplot2) #install.packages("ggplot2")

## subsetting data now

g <- gapminder %>% 
  filter(year == 2007) %>% 
  mutate(pop_m = pop/1e6)

My first plot

This is a simple geom_point

#ggplot needs (data, aes(whats x, whats y)) + what_kind_of_plot()
s <- ggplot(g, aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp)) +
              geom_point()
s

My second plot

This will be a simple geom_point with points related to size Following this, a plot with colours related to continent

#ggplot needs (data, aes(whats x, whats y)) + what_kind_of_plot()
s2 = s + aes(size = pop_m)

s2

s3 = s2 + aes(colour = continent)

s3

Pipey McPipeface

#ggplot needs (data, aes(whats x, whats y)) + what_kind_of_plot()
s <- ggplot(g, aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp)) +
  geom_point() +
  aes(size = pop_m) +
  aes(colour = continent) +
  ggtitle("Healthy McWealthface") + 
  xlab("GDP per capita ($/year)") +
  ylab("Life expectancy (years)") +
  scale_colour_discrete('Continent') +
  scale_size_continuous('Population (M)') 

s

Boxplot time

b <- ggplot(g, aes(x = continent, y = lifeExp)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  
  aes(fill = continent) +
  ggtitle("Boxy McPlotface") + 
  xlab("Continent") +
  ylab("Life expectancy (years)")+
  theme(legend.position = "none")

b

Making a GoogleVis figure

suppressPackageStartupMessages({
  library(googleVis) # install.packages('googleVis')
})                               
## Creating a generic function for 'toJSON' from package 'jsonlite' in package 'googleVis'
op <- options(gvis.plot.tag='chart')

m = gvisMotionChart(
  gapminder %>%
    mutate(
      pop_m = pop / 1e6,
      log_gdpPercap = log(gdpPercap)), 
  idvar='country', 
  timevar='year', 
  xvar='log_gdpPercap', 
  yvar='lifeExp', 
  colorvar='continent',
  sizevar='pop_m')
plot(m)
